WaterQ EDA

DISCLAIMER: Currently this is for PA only, I’ll start downloading NY/MD/VA.

Data prep

library(tidyverse)
library(sf)
library(boxr)

df <- boxr::box_read(533709206238, read_fun = readr::read_csv)

stat <- boxr::box_read(533624583956, read_fun = readr::read_csv) %>%
  select(MonitoringLocationIdentifier,LatitudeMeasure, LongitudeMeasure, HorizontalCoordinateReferenceSystemDatumName)

merged_df <- left_join(df, stat, by = 'MonitoringLocationIdentifier')

geo_df <- sf::st_as_sf(merged_df, coords = c('LongitudeMeasure','LatitudeMeasure'), crs = 4269)

Station count:

dplyr::n_distinct(geo_df$MonitoringLocationIdentifier)
FALSE [1] 6257

Locations

locations <- geo_df %>%
  group_by(MonitoringLocationIdentifier) %>%
  sample_n(1)

pa <- spData::us_states %>%
  filter(NAME == 'Pennsylvania') %>%
  st_transform(4269)

ggplot()+
  geom_sf(data = pa) +
  geom_sf(data =locations)

Streams

streams<-boxr::box_read(529764045834, read_fun = unzip) %>% 
  str_subset('.shp$') %>% 
  read_sf %>%
  st_transform(4269)

pa_streams <- st_intersection(streams, pa)

ggplot()+
  geom_sf(data = pa) +
  geom_sf(data = pa_streams, col = 'blue') +
  geom_sf(data =locations)

Types of measurements

library(DT)
merged_df %>%
  group_by(CharacteristicName) %>%
  summarise(n = n()) %>%
  DT::datatable(options = list("lengthMenu" = c(10, 25, 50, 100, 250, 500, "All")))

Number of stations that have a given measurement

merged_df %>%
  group_by(CharacteristicName) %>%
  summarise(num_stations = n_distinct(MonitoringLocationIdentifier)) %>%
  mutate(pct = num_stations / 6257) %>%
  DT::datatable(options = list("lengthMenu" = c(10, 25, 50, 100, 250, 500, "All")))

Leaflet map (note a lot of these stations don’t appear to be on streams…)

library(leaflet)
leafletlocs <- st_transform(locations, 4326)
leaflet() %>%
  leaflet::addProviderTiles('OpenStreetMap.Mapnik') %>%
  leaflet::addAwesomeMarkers(data = leafletlocs, label = ~MonitoringLocationIdentifier)
